commitResults.messageTitle: Level 0. Rename, Greet, Exit Change name of chatbot to Honey.  Implement an initial skeletal version of it that simply greets the user and exits. Add horizontal lines.
Level 1. Echo Improve the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye. Customized chatbot for uniqueness.
Level 0. Rename, Greet, Exit Change name of chatbot to Honey.  Implement an initial skeletal version of it that simply greets the user and exits. Add horizontal lines.
Level 1. Echo Improve the skeletal version of Duke so that it echos commands entered by the user, and exits when the user types the command bye. Customized chatbot for uniqueness.
Level 2. Add, List Add the ability to store whatever text entered by the user and display them back to the user when requested.
Level 3. Mark as Done Add the ability to mark tasks as done and back to undone. Implement Task Class.
A-TextUiTesting: Automated Text UI Testing Test using the I/O redirection technique
A-TextUiTesting: Automated Text UI Testing Use the input/output redirection technique to semi-automate the testing of Honey.
Level-5: Handle Errors Teach the chatbot to deal with errors such as incorrect inputs entered by the user.
Level-6: Delete Add support for deleting tasks from the list.
A-Enums:  Create TaskType enum to replace boolean flags Put Todo, Deadline and Event into TaskType enum to prevent invalid states

commitResults.messageBody: Save the tasks in the hard disk automatically whenever the task list changes. Load the data from the hard disk when the chatbot starts up.

Teach the chatbot how to understand dates and times. For example, if the command is deadline return book /by 2/12/2019 1800, the chatbot should understand 2/12/2019 1800 as 2nd of December 2019, 6pm, instead of treating it as just a String.
Make the code more OOP. Introduced new classes - Ui, Storage, Parser, TaskList, Command (abstract class), Other Command classes that inherit from the abstract Command class.
src/main/java is kept as the main source root folder. Created a main package honey, and subpackages: honey.command, honey.exceptions, honey.parser, honey.storage, honey.task, honey.tasklist, honey.ui

commitResults.messageBody:
# Conflicts:
#	src/main/java/honey/parser/Parser.java
#	src/main/java/honey/storage/Storage.java
#	src/main/java/honey/task/Task.java
#	src/main/java/honey/task/TaskType.java
#	src/main/java/honey/tasklist/TaskList.java
#	src/test/java/honey/command/CommandTest.java
#	src/test/java/honey/storage/StorageTest.java
#	src/test/java/honey/task/DeadlineTest.java
#	src/test/java/honey/task/EventTest.java
#	src/test/java/honey/task/TodoTest.java
#	src/test/java/honey/tasklist/TaskListTest.java
Refactor portions of code for better OOP and logic encapsulation as well as better use of enums. Additionally, adhered closely to the 'Code Quality' topics learn so far.

Use assert feature (not JUnit assertions) to document important assumptions that should hold at various points in the code. Primarily, focused on using assertion for:
1. Preconditions (parameters/inputs)
2. Postconditions (method results)
3. Invariants (state consistency)

Replace string concatenation for loop in findTasks() and findDueTasks() with streams filter and map function. Also, replaced enums string input matching for loop function with a stream findFirst() function.
Implement extension C-Sort to sort Deadline tasks in ascending order (i.e. task with closest deadline at the top). Task with deadlines overdue/passed will be labelled with [OVERDUE] in the task list.
